Reconstruction of Regulatory Interaction.p0:
To obtain gene regulatory interactions and reconstruct gene network (Fig.  1 c) from gene perturbation experiments, we developed a computational pipeline, which is divided into several steps. The z-scored perturbation expression profiles are represented as  Z j ∈ Z  with  j  = 1,…, n , in our case  n =591. Each profile  Z j  comprises  m j  biological replicates (usually between 2 and 4), which are repeated measurements of biologically distinct samples and capture random biological variation [ 14 ]. Each biological replicate is the average of  q k  technical replicates, which are repeated measurements of the same sample (usually between 4 and 6). A given perturbation experiment is represented as: 
